<section>
  <title><literal>InflectedForm</literal> object type</title>
  <para>
    An inflected headword is a form of the inflectional paradigm of its
    parent.
  </para>
  <para>
    Child of:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>Entry</literal>
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <para>
    Properties:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>label</literal> (non-empty string) e.g. 'plural'
      </para>
      <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
        <listitem>
          <para>Can be constrained and mapped to external authorities by the DMLex Controlled Vocabularies Module.</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>value</literal> (non-empty string)
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>listingOrder</literal>
      </para>
      <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
        <listitem>
          <para> Can be implicit from the serialization.</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <para>
    Children:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>Usage</literal> (zero or more)
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>Pronunciation</literal> (zero or more)
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <example>
    <title>Example of an entry with two inflected forms</title>
    <programlisting>Entry: headword="deirfiúr"
    PartOfSpeech: value="feminine noun"
    InflectedForm: label="genitive singular", value="deirféar"
    InflectedForm: label="plural", value="deirfiúracha"</programlisting>
  </example>
</section>
